{
  "_comment": "InMoov head expression library. Channel values are normalized: bipolar channels (eyePan,eyeTilt,yaw,pitch,roll) in [-1,1], jaw in [0,1]. ExpressionEngine maps each to the joint's real URDF limit, so this file is device-independent. 'idle' = amplitude of breathing/saccade micro-motion layered on top (0 = perfectly still). 'blend' = seconds to morph into the pose. Conventions: eyeTilt+ = look up, pitch+ = chin up, roll+ = tilt toward robot's right shoulder, yaw+ = turn robot-left, eyePan+ = eyes to robot-left, jaw 1 = mouth fully open.",
  "channels": ["eyePan", "eyeTilt", "jaw", "yaw", "pitch", "roll"],
  "expressions": {
    "neutral": {
      "label_zh": "中性",
      "channels": { "eyePan": 0, "eyeTilt": 0, "jaw": 0, "yaw": 0, "pitch": 0, "roll": 0 },
